## Mandatory Test Scenarios

### ✅ MUST Test: Schema Application

Every migration MUST verify schema changes apply successfully:

```typescript
test('should apply schema changes to database', async () => {
  // Arrange
  const testEventId = `test-event-${Date.now()}`
  
  // Act - Create event with new field
  await prismaClient.event.create({
    data: {
      id: testEventId,
      title: 'Test Event',
      isVerified: true, // New field
      // ... other fields
    }
  })
  
  // Assert - Verify field stored correctly
  const event = await prismaClient.event.findUnique({
    where: { id: testEventId }
  })
  
  expect(event).toBeTruthy()
  expect(event?.isVerified).toBe(true)
})
```

### ✅ MUST Test: Default Values

If migration adds columns with default values, MUST test:

```typescript
test('should apply default value to existing rows', async () => {
  // Arrange - Create event BEFORE migration (simulated)
  const existingEventId = `test-event-existing-${Date.now()}`
  await prismaClient.event.create({
    data: {
      id: existingEventId,
      title: 'Existing Event',
      // isVerified doesn't exist yet
    }
  })
  
  // Act - Run migration (in real test, migration already applied)
  // Migration adds: isVerified BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT false
  
  // Assert - Verify default value applied
  const event = await prismaClient.event.findUnique({
    where: { id: existingEventId }
  })
  
  expect(event?.isVerified).toBe(false) // Default value
})
```

### ✅ MUST Test: Constraint Enforcement

For NOT NULL, UNIQUE, CHECK, or FOREIGN KEY constraints:

```typescript
test('should enforce NOT NULL constraint on isVerified', async () => {
  // Arrange
  const testEventId = `test-event-${Date.now()}`
  
  // Act & Assert - Attempt to create without required field
  await expect(
    prismaClient.$executeRaw`
      INSERT INTO "Event" (id, title, "isVerified")
      VALUES (${testEventId}, 'Test', NULL)
    `
  ).rejects.toThrow(/NOT NULL constraint/)
})

test('should enforce UNIQUE constraint on email', async () => {
  // Arrange
  const email = `test-${Date.now()}@example.com`
  await prismaClient.user.create({
    data: { id: 'user1', email }
  })
  
  // Act & Assert - Attempt duplicate
  await expect(
    prismaClient.user.create({
      data: { id: 'user2', email }
    })
  ).rejects.toThrow(/UNIQUE constraint/)
})

test('should enforce FOREIGN KEY constraint', async () => {
  // Arrange
  const nonExistentCityId = 'city-does-not-exist'
  
  // Act & Assert - Attempt to reference non-existent row
  await expect(
    prismaClient.event.create({
      data: {
        id: 'event1',
        title: 'Test Event',
        cityId: nonExistentCityId, // FK violation
      }
    })
  ).rejects.toThrow(/FOREIGN KEY constraint/)
})
```

### ✅ MUST Test: Index Creation

For CREATE INDEX migrations:

```typescript
test('should create index on Event.isVerified', async () => {
  // Query database for index information
  const indexes = await prismaClient.$queryRaw<Array<{ indexname: string }>>`
    SELECT indexname 
    FROM pg_indexes 
    WHERE tablename = 'Event' 
    AND indexname = 'Event_isVerified_idx'
  `
  
  expect(indexes).toHaveLength(1)
  expect(indexes[0].indexname).toBe('Event_isVerified_idx')
})

test('should use index for isVerified queries', async () => {
  // Get query execution plan
  const plan = await prismaClient.$queryRaw<Array<{ 'QUERY PLAN': string }>>`
    EXPLAIN SELECT * FROM "Event" WHERE "isVerified" = true
  `
  
  const planText = plan.map(p => p['QUERY PLAN']).join('\n')
  
  // Verify index is used (not sequential scan)
  expect(planText).toContain('Index Scan')
  expect(planText).toContain('Event_isVerified_idx')
})
```

### ✅ MUST Test: Data Transformations

For migrations that update existing data:

```typescript
test('should transform existing profile URLs correctly', async () => {
  // Arrange - Create profiles with old format
  const profile1Id = `test-profile-1-${Date.now()}`
  const profile2Id = `test-profile-2-${Date.now()}`
  
  await prismaClient.instagramProfile.createMany({
    data: [
      { instagramId: profile1Id, username: 'user1', profileUrl: '' },
      { instagramId: profile2Id, username: 'user2', profileUrl: '' },
    ]
  })
  
  // Act - Run data transformation (migration script)
  await prismaClient.$executeRaw`
    UPDATE "InstagramProfile"
    SET "profileUrl" = CONCAT('https://instagram.com/', username)
    WHERE "profileUrl" = ''
  `
  
  // Assert - Verify transformation
  const profile1 = await prismaClient.instagramProfile.findUnique({
    where: { instagramId: profile1Id }
  })
  const profile2 = await prismaClient.instagramProfile.findUnique({
    where: { instagramId: profile2Id }
  })
  
  expect(profile1?.profileUrl).toBe('https://instagram.com/user1')
  expect(profile2?.profileUrl).toBe('https://instagram.com/user2')
})

test('should handle NULL values in data transformation', async () => {
  // Arrange - Create row with NULL
  const profileId = `test-profile-null-${Date.now()}`
  await prismaClient.$executeRaw`
    INSERT INTO "InstagramProfile" (instagram_id, username, profile_url)
    VALUES (${profileId}, NULL, '')
  `
  
  // Act - Run transformation that must handle NULL
  await prismaClient.$executeRaw`
    UPDATE "InstagramProfile"
    SET "profileUrl" = COALESCE(CONCAT('https://instagram.com/', username), 'https://instagram.com/unknown')
    WHERE "profileUrl" = ''
  `
  
  // Assert
  const profile = await prismaClient.instagramProfile.findUnique({
    where: { instagramId: profileId }
  })
  
  expect(profile?.profileUrl).toBe('https://instagram.com/unknown')
})
```

### ✅ MUST Test: Rollback Safety

Every migration MUST verify it can be safely rolled back:

```typescript
test('should rollback migration without data loss', async () => {
  // Arrange - Create test data with new schema
  const eventId = `test-event-rollback-${Date.now()}`
  await prismaClient.event.create({
    data: {
      id: eventId,
      title: 'Test Event',
      isVerified: true,
      // ... other fields
    }
  })
  
  // Act - Simulate rollback by dropping column
  await prismaClient.$executeRaw`
    ALTER TABLE "Event" DROP COLUMN IF EXISTS "isVerified"
  `
  
  // Assert - Verify other data preserved
  const event = await prismaClient.event.findUnique({
    where: { id: eventId }
  })
  
  expect(event).toBeTruthy()
  expect(event?.title).toBe('Test Event')
  // isVerified field should not exist after rollback
  expect('isVerified' in event!).toBe(false)
  
  // Cleanup - Re-apply migration for other tests
  await prismaClient.$executeRaw`
    ALTER TABLE "Event" ADD COLUMN "isVerified" BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT false
  `
})
```

### ✅ MUST Test: Application Compatibility

Verify domain layer handles new schema:

```typescript
describe('Event Entity - isVerified field compatibility', () => {
  test('should create event with isVerified field', () => {
    // Arrange
    const eventData = {
      id: EventId.generate(),
      title: Title.create('Concert'),
      isVerified: false,
    }
    
    // Act
    const event = Event.create(eventData)
    
    // Assert
    expect(event).toBeInstanceOf(Event)
    expect(event.getIsVerified()).toBe(false)
  })
  
  test('should convert event with isVerified to DTO', () => {
    // Arrange
    const event = Event.create({
      id: EventId.generate(),
      title: Title.create('Festival'),
      isVerified: true,
    })
    
    // Act
    const dto = event.toDto()
    
    // Assert
    expect(dto.isVerified).toBe(true)
  })
  
  test('should create event from database with isVerified', () => {
    // Arrange
    const dbRow = {
      id: 'event-123',
      title: 'Concert',
      isVerified: false,
      // ... other fields
    }
    
    // Act
    const event = Event.fromDatabase(dbRow)
    
    // Assert
    expect(event.getIsVerified()).toBe(false)
  })
})
```

## Migration Testing Workflow

### Complete TDD Workflow for Migrations

```
1. Identify schema change need
   ↓
2. STEP 0: REASON
   - Plan migration changes
   - List test cases (in test file as comments)
   - Order simple → complex
   ↓
3. STEP 1: RED
   - Write failing unit test (domain entities)
   - Write failing integration test (database operations)
   - Verify tests fail (migration doesn't exist)
   ↓
4. STEP 2: GREEN
   - Create migration file: bunx prisma migrate dev --name <name>
   - Update domain entities/repositories
   - Verify tests pass
   ↓
5. STEP 3: REFACTOR
   - Optimize migration SQL
   - Improve domain code
   - Keep tests green
   ↓
6. STEP 4: RE-EVALUATE
   - Review test cases list
   - Verify 80-90% coverage
   - Return to RED if gaps exist
   ↓
7. Run Biome check on all edited files
   ↓
8. Submit PR with tests + migration
```

### Database Setup for Migration Tests

Migration integration tests MUST use separate test database:

```typescript
describe('Migration: 20251215_add_is_verified_to_event', () => {
  let prismaClient: PrismaClientEy
  const testPrefix = 'test-migration-'
  
  beforeEach(async () => {
    // MANDATORY: Verify TEST_DATABASE_URL exists
    if (!process.env.TEST_DATABASE_URL) {
      throw new Error(
        'TEST_DATABASE_URL is required for migration tests. ' +
        'Set TEST_DATABASE_URL to separate test database.'
      )
    }
    
    // Create client with test database
    prismaClient = new PrismaClientEy({
      datasources: {
        db: { url: process.env.TEST_DATABASE_URL }
      }
    })
    
    // Clean database before test
    await cleanupTestData()
  })
  
  afterEach(async () => {
    // Clean database after test
    await cleanupTestData()
    await prismaClient.$disconnect()
  })
  
  async function cleanupTestData() {
    try {
      // Delete test data by prefix
      await prismaClient.event.deleteMany({
        where: { id: { startsWith: testPrefix } }
      })
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Cleanup failed:', error)
      throw error
    }
  }
  
  // Tests here...
})
```

