## Coverage Requirements

### Minimum Coverage: 80-90% of Critical Paths

**Critical paths that MUST be tested:**
1. ✅ Schema changes apply successfully
2. ✅ Constraints enforce rules correctly
3. ✅ Default values work as expected
4. ✅ Indexes improve query performance
5. ✅ Data transformations preserve integrity
6. ✅ Rollback preserves data
7. ✅ Application code handles new schema

**Lower priority (may skip if simple):**
- Rare edge cases (e.g., extremely long strings if max length validated elsewhere)
- Performance benchmarks (unless index specifically added for performance)
- Cosmetic changes (e.g., renaming columns without logic changes)

### Coverage Measurement

Run test coverage to verify:

```bash
# Run migration tests with coverage
bun test prisma/migrations/__tests__ --coverage

# Verify coverage ≥80% for:
# - Schema application functions
# - Constraint enforcement
# - Data transformation scripts
# - Rollback procedures
```

## PR Checklist

Before submitting a PR with database migrations, verify:

### Migration Testing Checklist

- [ ] **Tests written BEFORE migration file** (TDD cycle followed)
- [ ] **Unit tests exist** for affected domain entities/value objects
- [ ] **Integration tests verify** database operations
- [ ] **Schema application tested** (new columns/tables created)
- [ ] **Constraint enforcement tested** (NOT NULL, UNIQUE, FK, CHECK)
- [ ] **Default values tested** (applied to existing rows)
- [ ] **Indexes tested** (created and used by queries)
- [ ] **Data transformations tested** (if migration updates existing data)
- [ ] **Rollback tested** (migration can be safely reverted)
- [ ] **Application compatibility tested** (domain code handles new schema)
- [ ] **Test coverage ≥80%** for critical paths
- [ ] **All tests pass** in TEST_DATABASE_URL
- [ ] **Biome check passes** for all test files
- [ ] **Tests in PR** alongside migration files

### Migration File Requirements

- [ ] Migration name is descriptive (`add_is_verified_to_event`, not `migration_123`)
- [ ] Migration SQL is idempotent where possible
- [ ] Migration includes comments explaining purpose
- [ ] Migration handles edge cases (NULL, empty strings, etc.)
- [ ] Migration optimized (e.g., CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY if needed)

### Documentation Requirements

- [ ] Migration purpose documented in commit message
- [ ] Breaking changes documented (if any)
- [ ] Data transformation steps documented (if any)
- [ ] Rollback procedure documented (if complex)

## Exceptions

### When Migration Tests May Be Simplified

**Rare exceptions where full test suite may be reduced:**

1. **Purely additive optional columns** with no constraints
   - May skip constraint tests if column is nullable with no default
   - Still MUST test schema application and application compatibility

2. **Cosmetic changes** (column renames without logic changes)
   - May skip constraint/index tests if unchanged
   - Still MUST test application compatibility

3. **Index-only changes** with no schema modifications
   - May skip constraint tests
   - Still MUST test index creation and query usage

**Even with exceptions:**
- ❌ NEVER skip all tests
- ❌ NEVER skip application compatibility tests
- ❌ NEVER skip rollback tests
- ✅ ALWAYS write at least basic schema application test
- ✅ ALWAYS follow TDD cycle (tests first)

### Exceptions Require Approval

If you believe your migration qualifies for simplified testing:
1. Document reasoning in PR description
2. Request Technical Lead approval
3. Still write minimum viable test suite
4. Document what tests were skipped and why

## Enforcement

### FORBIDDEN Actions

- ❌ **Creating migration file without tests**
- ❌ **Running `bunx prisma migrate dev` without tests passing**
- ❌ **Submitting PR with migration but no tests**
- ❌ **Skipping rollback tests**
- ❌ **Using production/development database for tests**
- ❌ **Deleting or modifying tests to make migration "pass"**

### REQUIRED Actions

- ✅ **Write tests FIRST** (TDD cycle)
- ✅ **Follow REASON-RED-GREEN-REFACTOR-RE-EVALUATE cycle**
- ✅ **Use TEST_DATABASE_URL for migration tests**
- ✅ **Achieve 80-90% coverage of critical paths**
- ✅ **Include tests in PR with migration**
- ✅ **Run Biome check on all test files**
- ✅ **Document test coverage in PR description**

## Commands

### Setup Test Database

```bash
# Create test database (run once)
createdb mato_test

# Run migrations on test database
TEST_DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/mato_test" \
  bunx prisma migrate deploy

# Reset test database when needed
TEST_DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/mato_test" \
  bunx prisma migrate reset --force
```

### Run Migration Tests

```bash
# Run all migration tests
TEST_DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/mato_test" \
  bun test prisma/migrations/__tests__

# Run specific migration test
TEST_DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/mato_test" \
  bun test prisma/migrations/__tests__/20251215_add_is_verified.integration.test.ts

# Run with coverage
TEST_DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/mato_test" \
  bun test prisma/migrations/__tests__ --coverage

# Run with logger output
TEST_DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/mato_test" \
  TEST_LOGGER=1 bun test prisma/migrations/__tests__
```

### Create Migration (After Tests Pass)

```bash
# Generate migration with descriptive name
bunx prisma migrate dev --name add_is_verified_to_event

# Apply migrations to test database
TEST_DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/mato_test" \
  bunx prisma migrate deploy

# Generate Prisma client
bun db:generate
```

